<paragraph id="8B8236C7FFB3FF99FFEAFC996A5CFAE1" blockId="49.[151,1437,674,1711]" pageId="49" pageNumber="50">
<emphasis id="B949EAD5FFB3FF99FFEAFC9969CEFC8C" bold="true" box="[199,444,818,844]" pageId="49" pageNumber="50">Revised description.</emphasis>
Shell small, solid, moderately broad buccinoid with conical spire; apical angle ~43°. Protoconch paucispiral of one whorl. Teleoconch of up to nine whorls. Early teleoconch whorls flat-sided, bearing weakly opisthocline axial ribs with tripartite sculpture; two beaded adsutural spiral cords, separated by narrower beaded central cord. Subsutural cord becoming coarsely tuberculose, central and suprasutural band with smaller tubercles, further finely granular secondary spirals intercalated. Suture narrowly impressed, undulating. Last whorl 65% of total height, subcylindrical to weakly ovoid; subsutural collar broad, poorly delimited, weakly tuberculose. Subsutural ramp weakly concave, narrow, with beaded cord running at mid-ramp. Shoulder poorly defined by beaded cord, weakly convex below, weakly angular at peribasal cord. Base weakly constricted. Siphonal fasciole moderately swollen, twisted. Peribasal and perifasciolar cords weakly tuberculose, the tubercles aligned axially to form indistinct axial riblets, with numerous secondary cords of irregular strength intercalated over entire whorl. Aperture wide, ovate. Outer lip not thickened, smooth within. Anal sinus wide, deep, symmetrically U-shaped. Apex coinciding with row of beads mid-ramp. Siphonal canal moderately short, shallowly notched at tip. Columella weakly excavated in upper third, straight below, smooth. Columellar and parietal callus strongly thickened, sharply delimited, forming broad callus rim.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C327654CFFB3FF99FFEAFA816BB8F9A6" pageId="49" pageNumber="50" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="8B8236C7FFB3FF99FFEAFA816C51FA4D" blockId="49.[151,1437,674,1711]" pageId="49" pageNumber="50">
<emphasis id="B949EAD5FFB3FF99FFEAFA81693EFA84" bold="true" box="[199,332,1322,1348]" pageId="49" pageNumber="50">Discussion.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="4C3D4D44FFB3FF99FE7BFA806B13FA85" authority="(Svagrovsky, 1958)" authorityName="Harzhauser &amp; Landau &amp; Janssen" authorityYear="2022" baseAuthorityName="Svagrovsky" baseAuthorityYear="1958" box="[342,865,1322,1351]" class="Gastropoda" family="Clavatulidae" genus="Granulatocincta" kingdom="Animalia" order="Neogastropoda" pageId="49" pageNumber="50" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="contorta">
<emphasis id="B949EAD5FFB3FF99FE7BFA806A0AFA84" box="[342,632,1323,1349]" italics="true" pageId="49" pageNumber="50">Granulatocincta contorta</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation id="EFAC4B36FFB3FF99FDA4FA876B2BFA85" author="Svagrovsky, J." box="[649,857,1322,1351]" pageId="49" pageNumber="50" pagination="5 - 56" refId="ref145176" refString="Svagrovsky, J. (1958) Miocenne Pleurotomidae zapadokarpatskych panvi (Miozane Pleurotomidae der westkarpatischen Becken). Acta Geologica et Geographica Universitatis Comenianae, Geologica, 1, 5 - 56." type="journal article" year="1958">Švagrovský, 1958</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
is slightly reminiscent of 
<taxonomicName id="4C3D4D44FFB3FF99FBBEFA806DEEFA85" authority="Harzhauser &amp; Landau &amp; Janssen, 2022" authorityName="Harzhauser &amp; Landau &amp; Janssen" authorityYear="2022" box="[1171,1436,1323,1349]" class="Gastropoda" family="Clavatulidae" genus="Granulatocincta" kingdom="Animalia" order="Neogastropoda" pageId="49" pageNumber="50" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="callim" status="nov. sp.">
<emphasis id="B949EAD5FFB3FF99FBBEFA806DEEFA85" box="[1171,1436,1323,1349]" italics="true" pageId="49" pageNumber="50">Granulatocincta callim</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A27A57AEFFB3FF99FFBAFAE4689FFAA9" box="[151,237,1359,1385]" pageId="49" pageNumber="50" rank="species">nov. sp.</taxonomicNameLabel>
The general mode of sculpture is similar in the two species, but 
<taxonomicName id="4C3D4D44FFB3FF99FCEDFAE46C5AFAA9" authorityName="Harzhauser &amp; Landau &amp; Janssen" authorityYear="2022" box="[960,1064,1359,1385]" class="Gastropoda" family="Clavatulidae" genus="Granulatocincta" kingdom="Animalia" order="Neogastropoda" pageId="49" pageNumber="50" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="callim">
<emphasis id="B949EAD5FFB3FF99FCEDFAE46C5AFAA9" box="[960,1064,1359,1385]" italics="true" pageId="49" pageNumber="50">G. callim</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
differs in its more subcylindrical last whorl and the sculpture of 
<taxonomicName id="4C3D4D44FFB3FF99FEDFFAD86A28FA4D" authorityName="Harzhauser &amp; Landau &amp; Janssen" authorityYear="2022" box="[498,602,1395,1421]" class="Gastropoda" family="Clavatulidae" genus="Granulatocincta" kingdom="Animalia" order="Neogastropoda" pageId="49" pageNumber="50" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="callim">
<emphasis id="B949EAD5FFB3FF99FEDFFAD86A28FA4D" box="[498,602,1395,1421]" italics="true" pageId="49" pageNumber="50">G. callim</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is distinctly more crowded and stronger.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8B8236C7FFB3FF99FFEAFA3C6CAFF981" blockId="49.[151,1437,674,1711]" pageId="49" pageNumber="50">
The Tortonian, Proto-Mediterranean 
<taxonomicName id="4C3D4D44FFB3FF99FD43FA3C6C29FA71" authority="(Michelotti, 1847)" baseAuthorityName="Michelotti" baseAuthorityYear="1847" box="[622,1115,1431,1457]" class="Gastropoda" family="Clavatulidae" genus="Granulatocincta" kingdom="Animalia" order="Neogastropoda" pageId="49" pageNumber="50" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="sotterii">
<emphasis id="B949EAD5FFB3FF99FD43FA3C6BF2FA70" box="[622,896,1431,1457]" italics="true" pageId="49" pageNumber="50">Granulatocincta sotterii</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation id="EFAC4B36FFB3FF99FCBFFA3C6C21FA71" author="Michelotti, G." box="[914,1107,1431,1457]" pageId="49" pageNumber="50" pagination="1 - 408" refId="ref138690" refString="Michelotti, G. (1847) Description des fossiles des terrains miocenes de l'Italie septentrionale. Natuurkundige Verhandelingen van de Hollandsche Maatschappij der Wetenschappen te Haarlem, Series 2, 3 (2), 1 - 408. [https: // books. google. be / books? id = aQVqpL 58 HrsC &amp; ots = rhEPJ _ C 6 hy &amp; dq = Michelotti % 2 C % 20 G. % 091847 % 09 Description % 20 des % 20 fossiles % 20 de s % 20 terrains % 20 mioc % C 3 % A 8 nes % 20 de % 20 l'Italie % 20 septentrionale. &amp; lr &amp; pg = PP 5  v = onepage &amp; q = Michelotti, % 20 G. % 091847 % 09 Description % 20 des % 2]" type="journal article" year="1847">Michelotti, 1847</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
is similar, but differs in its more crowded sculpture, much more prominent beads and more convex last whorl (see 
<bibRefCitation id="EFAC4B36FFB3FF99FB51FA106D00FA15" author="Montanaro, E." box="[1148,1394,1467,1493]" pageId="49" pageNumber="50" pagination="115 - 191" refId="ref139628" refString="Montanaro, E. (1937) Studi monografici sulla malacologia miocenica modenese. Parte I. I mollusci tortoniani di Montegibbio. Palaeontographia Italica, New Series 7, 37, 115 - 191." type="journal article" year="1937">Montanaro 1937: 117</bibRefCitation>
, pl. 5, figs 2–18; 
<bibRefCitation id="EFAC4B36FFB3FF99FE06FA746A4CFA39" author="Ruggieri, C. &amp; Davoli, F." box="[299,574,1503,1529]" pageId="49" pageNumber="50" pagination="41 - 85" refId="ref142914" refString="Ruggieri, C. &amp; Davoli, F. (1984) Malacofauna di Casa Nova Calisese (Sogliano, Forli), Palaeontographia Italica, 73, 41 - 85." type="journal article" year="1984">Ruggieri &amp; Davoli 1984</bibRefCitation>
, pl. 4, figs 1, 6, 13–14, 18–19, 
<bibRefCitation id="EFAC4B36FFB3FF99FCB4FA746C55FA39" author="Davoli, F." box="[921,1063,1503,1529]" pageId="49" pageNumber="50" pagination="27 - 109" refId="ref131183" refString="Davoli, F. (1990) La collezione di &quot; Fossili Miocenici di Sogliano &quot; di Ludovico Foresti: revisione ed illustrazione. Atti della Societa dei Naturalisti e Matematici di Modena, 121, 27 - 109." type="journal article" year="1990">Davoli 1990</bibRefCitation>
, pl. 8, figs 2–8). 
<taxonomicName id="4C3D4D44FFB3FF99FBCEFA74694AF9DD" authority="Harzhauser &amp; Landau &amp; Janssen, 2022" authorityName="Harzhauser &amp; Landau &amp; Janssen" authorityYear="2022" class="Gastropoda" family="Clavatulidae" genus="Granulatocincta" kingdom="Animalia" order="Neogastropoda" pageId="49" pageNumber="50" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="pelliscrocodili" status="nov. sp.">
<emphasis id="B949EAD5FFB3FF99FBCEFA74694AF9DD" italics="true" pageId="49" pageNumber="50">Granulatocincta pelliscrocodili</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A27A57AEFFB3FF99FE12F9A869E5F9DD" box="[319,407,1539,1565]" pageId="49" pageNumber="50" rank="species">nov. sp.</taxonomicNameLabel>
, from the Serravallian of 
<collectingCountry id="F32A7657FFB3FF99FD95F9A86B7BF9DD" box="[696,777,1539,1565]" name="Turkey" pageId="49" pageNumber="50">Turkey</collectingCountry>
, might be a related species, but differs from 
<taxonomicName id="4C3D4D44FFB3FF99FBD3F9A86D0DF9DC" authorityName="Harzhauser &amp; Landau &amp; Janssen" authorityYear="2022" baseAuthorityName="Svagrovsky" baseAuthorityYear="1958" box="[1278,1407,1539,1565]" class="Gastropoda" family="Clavatulidae" genus="Granulatocincta" kingdom="Animalia" order="Neogastropoda" pageId="49" pageNumber="50" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="contorta">
<emphasis id="B949EAD5FFB3FF99FBD3F9A86D0DF9DC" box="[1278,1407,1539,1565]" italics="true" pageId="49" pageNumber="50">G. contorta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in its stout shape, the even weaker beads and the delicate spiral sculpture, which overruns the beads.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8B8236C7FFB3FF99FFEAF9E16BB8F9A6" blockId="49.[151,1437,674,1711]" box="[199,970,1610,1639]" pageId="49" pageNumber="50">
<emphasis id="B949EAD5FFB3FF99FFEAF9E169DAF9A4" bold="true" box="[199,424,1610,1636]" pageId="49" pageNumber="50">Paleoenvironment.</emphasis>
Inner neritic environments (
<bibRefCitation id="EFAC4B36FFB3FF99FDCBF9E76BCCF9A6" author="Svagrovsky, J." box="[742,958,1611,1639]" pageId="49" pageNumber="50" pagination="1 - 216" refId="ref145266" refString="Svagrovsky, J. (1960 b) Biostratigrafia a fauna makkysov vrchneho Tortonu vychodneho upatia Slanskych hor. Geologicke Prace, 57, 1 - 216." type="journal article" year="1960">Švagrovský 1960b</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C327654CFFB3FF99FFEAF9C56AFBF96E" pageId="49" pageNumber="50" type="distribution">
